<plot>Some Apologies begins with a confession: "Once, when I was little, I hit my brother in the face." Like all confessions, the statement is the first step into a maze of self-examination and doubt. Using introspective first-person narration and enchanting nostalgic imagery, the film explores the darker side of childhood and brotherly love.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?505637</url></doc>
